creator: Sara Teasdale
description:
LibriVox recording of Love Songs by Sara Teasdale.
Read in English by Sonia; Jacqui Castle; Gaby; Ryan Finch; Lian Pang; Carol; Kalynda; Shakira Searle; Livia F.; Tomas Peter; Kathleen Moore; Ian King; Rehj
"Sara Teasdale sings about love better than any other contemporary American poet."—'The Boston Transcript', 1918.
As the title already gives away, this is a volume of love poetry by Sara Teasdale, the first volume of poetry ever to be awarded the Pulitzer Prize for poetry in 1918. - Summary by Carolin
For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B Audiobook (29MB)
